PrecisApproval of the appointment by the Minister of Supply and Services of certain persons as directors of the Board of Directors of the Canada Post Corporation to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years, effective August 31, 1994. (Paul A. Tremblay, Cap-Rouge, Quebec, in the place of Pierre Roy, whose term has expired; and Hélène Lorrain-Tardif, Sainte-Julie, Quebec, in the place of Micheline Bouchard, whose term has expired)
